President Trump held a joint press conference with Italian President Mattarella at the White House. Trump discussed various topics including the recent $7.5 billion award against the European Union, trade deals with Italy, the situation in Syria and Turkey, and the impeachment inquiry. Trump emphasized the strong relationship between the US and Italy and expressed confidence in the safety of nuclear weapons at Incirlik Air Base in Turkey. He also mentioned his meeting with the family of Harry Dunn, the British teenager who was killed in a car crash involving the wife of a US diplomat. Trump offered his condolences to the family but mentioned that they did not want to meet with the person involved in the crash.